msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Now let's think more about negative consequences. Which of these consequences do you feel is appropriate?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Not seeing any friends for a month"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"This may be hard to do for you and also too harsh! \n"
"\n"
"Remember, consequences should be fair, immediate and consistent."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Cancelling their birthday plans in a month's time"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"This is too far in the future and too harsh as well! \n"
"\n"
"Remember, consequences should be fair, immediate and consistent."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No TV this evening"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Perfect, this sounds fair and can be done straight away."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"It is time to learn and practise!\n"
"\n"
"Plan a calm consequence for your teenagers arguing with each other during dinner."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"**Remember, consequences should be:** \n"
"⚖️ FAIR (not too harsh) \n"
"💨 IMMEDIATE (do it straight away) \n"
"🎯 CONSISTENT (same every time)"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Can you agree on one NEGATIVE consequence and one POSITIVE consequence with your teen?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That's fantastic! When teens help choose their own consequences - both positive and negative - they are more likely to understand and stick to them. You are helping them grow into a responsible young adult."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "I think so"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That’s a great start! Take your time - you can come up with ideas together step by step."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That's okay. These conversations can be tricky at first. Keep spending time together and try again when the moment feels right. You are already on the right path."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "When consequences are calm, clear, and agreed on together, teens are more likely to follow the rules. They will feel respected, not punished, and that is the best way to help our teens learn."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.media_daughter_6.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Tap play to hear how @data.characters.media_daughter_6.name learned to appreciate calm consequences"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"My mom and dad would always punish me when they were angry with me. They would shout at me and I would also get angry. I often did not follow the rules, because they were too harsh, I did not understand what they were saying, or I would not even bother listening to them, because we were all angry.\n"
"\n"
"One day, they asked me: Let's think together what the consequence should be for not coming home in time. It was great to give my view – before something happens that makes us all angry. We are all calm and agree first. It is easier for me to follow the rules now because I know I agreed on the rule and on the consequence if I do not follow the rule."
msgstr ""
